A lead is raw contact (name, email, phone) and doesn't indicate real interest.

A qualified appointment instead:
• Is already scheduled on your agenda;
• Respects ICP parameters;
• The interlocutor knows why they're contacted and is interested in a meeting;
• Validity is objective: if it doesn't respect ICP or no-show, it's not counted or replaced based on package.

• ADV require increasing budgets and reduced margins;
• Network/word-of-mouth are neither predictable nor scalable.

By multiplying contact points, response increases and the flow of opportunities stabilizes.

